2026-01-23: Type-erased DynDataset wrapper

Problem:
  Dataset<float, int32_t> forces template types through all downstream code.
  Goal: specify types once at open site, then work with a non-templated interface.

What was done:

1. Created gits/mmappet/src/mmappet/cpp/mmappet/mmappet_dyn.h

   New header implementing three components:

   - element_size_from_type_str(): maps type strings ("float32", "int32", etc.)
     to byte sizes (4, 4, etc.).

   - Column (non-templated, move-only): wraps one mmap'd .bin file as raw bytes.
     RAII: munmap + close in destructor. Provides name(), type_str(), size(),
     element_size(), raw_data(), and as<T>() for typed access with runtime check.

   - DynDataset (non-templated, move-only): holds std::vector<Column>.
     Provides operator[](size_t), operator[](string_view) for name lookup,
     num_columns(), num_rows(), begin()/end() for iteration.

   - TypedDataset<T, Args...> : public DynDataset: adds typed_columns()
     returning std::tuple<std::span<const T>, std::span<const Args>...>.
     Static factory open(path, col_names) reads schema.txt, validates types
     and names match template args, mmaps each .bin into a Column.

   Includes mmappet.h for get_type_str<T>() and split_first_space().

2. Created gits/examples/test_dyn_dataset.cpp

   Test program demonstrating:
   - TypedDataset<float, int32_t>::open() with column name validation
   - Structured bindings via typed_columns()
   - Passing TypedDataset to a function taking DynDataset& (no templates)
   - Column lookup by name
   - Storing in std::vector<std::unique_ptr<DynDataset>>

3. Modified gits/Makefile

   Added DYN_SRC, DYN_BIN variables and build rule.
   Added .PHONY target "test_dyn_dataset" for convenience.
   Added $(DYN_BIN) to the "all" target.

4. Updated SPECIFICATION

   Added test_dyn_dataset to the project tree (build/ and examples/).
   Added mmappet_dyn.h to the mmappet/src tree.
   Documented the Column, DynDataset, and TypedDataset interfaces.

Build & test:
  cd gits
  make                           # builds all three binaries
  ./build/test_dataset_writer    # creates example/dataset.mmappet/
  ./build/test_dyn_dataset       # opens dataset via TypedDataset, prints values

One compile fix applied:
  Used .template as<U>() in typed_columns_impl() because columns_[idx]
  is a dependent expression (idx is a non-type template parameter).
